7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Google Translate and Weglot share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Api Access, Real Time. Where Google Translate pulls ahead is with exclusive access to File Formats, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Weglot uniquely offers Glossary and Team Collaboration and Cms Integration, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Google Translate holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while Weglot scores 8/10 overall and 10/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Google Translate offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Weglot's starting price of $15/mo. Google Translate has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Weglot does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
